## What `process_line/2` must do

`process_line/2` is the reducer passed to `Enum.reduce/3` inside
`build_categories/1`. It folds the stream of *classified* lines into the
accumulating result. Each classified line is one of `{:heading, name}`,
`{:item, item_map}`, or `:ignore`, and the accumulator (the state) is a map of
the shape:

```elixir
%{categories: [finalised_category_map, ...], current: current_category_or_nil}
```

where `categories` holds already-completed category maps in **reverse** document
order, and `current` is the category currently being built (`%{category: name,
items: [...]}` with `items` prepended, i.e. reversed) or `nil` if no `##`
heading has been seen yet.

Implement the three cases:

1. **`{:heading, name}`** — a new H2 heading begins a new category. If there is a
   `current` category in progress, finalise it with `finalise/1` and prepend the
   result to `categories`; if `current` is `nil`, leave `categories` untouched.
   Either way, set `current` to a fresh `%{category: name, items: []}`.

2. **`{:item, item}`** — a valid bullet item. If a `current` category exists,
   prepend `item` onto its `items` list (use `Map.update!/3`) and keep
   `categories` unchanged. If `current` is `nil` (the item appeared before any
   heading), discard the item: return the state unchanged.

3. **`:ignore`** — any unrecognised line. Return the state unchanged.

The function must return an updated state map of the same shape so the reduction
can continue.

